        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): replace hardcoded \"--\" with FLAG_TERMINATOR constant in getCommandPathInternal",
        "body": "\n## Summary\n\nReplace the sole remaining hardcoded `\"--\"` literal in `getCommandPathInternal` with the `FLAG_TERMINATOR` constant already imported and used by every other function in `argv.ts`.\n\nPrevents silent subcommand-routing divergence if `FLAG_TERMINATOR` is ever changed.\n\n**Addressed review feedback (ClawSweeper P3):** Reworded the regression test comment to accurately describe what it proves (integration with the constant), since the test cannot independently detect a literal regression while `FLAG_TERMINATOR` remains `\"--\"`. The companion contract test asserts the canonical value.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #83902\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** `getCommandPathInternal` used a hardcoded `\"--\"` string while all other functions in the same file use the `FLAG_TERMINATOR` constant.\n- **Real environment tested:** macOS, Node v22.22.3, latest upstream/main (050c0813b)\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```bash\nnpx tsx proof-89897.mjs\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix (copied live output):**\n\n```\n=== Live Proof: #89897 / #83902 ===\nFLAG_TERMINATOR constant: \"--\"\n\nCase 1: getCommandPath([node, openclaw, channels, --, add], 2)\n  Result: [channels]\n  PASS: true\n\nCase 2: getCommandPath([node, openclaw, channels, add], 2)\n  Result: [channels, add]\n  PASS: true\n\nCase 3: getCommandPath([node, openclaw, config, --, set, --key, value], 2)\n  Result: [config]\n  PASS: true\n\nCase 4: getCommandPathWithRootOptions([node, openclaw, --debug, status, --, extra], 2)\n  Result: [status]\n  PASS: true\n\nCase 5: FLAG_TERMINATOR === \"--\"\n  PASS: true\n\n=== Live Proof #89897: ALL PASSED ===\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** FLAG_TERMINATOR correctly stops command-path parsing. Command-path resolution is consistent with all other argv helpers.\n- **What was not tested:** N/A — single-line refactor with focused regression tests and live CLI behavior proof.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n**Which commands did you run?**\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/cli/argv.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n# 112 passed (1 test file)\n```\n\n**What regression coverage was added or updated?**\n- `\"uses FLAG_TERMINATOR constant to stop command-path parsing\"` — exercises integration with the imported constant\n- `\"FLAG_TERMINATOR is the canonical -- string\"` — contract test asserting the canonical value\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n**Did user-visible behavior change?** No\n**Did config, environment, or migration behavior change?** No\n**Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change?** No\n**What is the highest-risk area?** None — identical runtime behavior (same constant value `\"--\"`).\n**How is that risk mitigated?** 112 argv tests pass; the contract test explicitly asserts the canonical value.\n\n## Current review state\n\n**What is the next action?** Requesting ClawSweeper re-review.\n**What is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?** None — live CLI behavior proof added.\n\n---\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com>\n",
